.\" CSCHOOL(420) Manual Page - Mouse-Free Terminal Guide
.TH CSCHOOL 420 "May 6, 2026" "C-SCHOOL" "C-SCHOOL Manual"
.SH NAME
school \\- C-SCHOOL terminal and keybinding guide
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B school
[command]
.SH DESCRIPTION
C-SCHOOL provides an optional mouse-free terminal experience inspired by vim.
This guide covers keybindings for users who want to navigate without a mouse.
This is NOT required \\- mouse usage is always supported.
.SH MOUSE-FREE BASICS
.PP
The terminal is your primary interface. Here are the essential keybinds:
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B Ctrl+a
Jump to beginning of line (instead of clicking line start)
.TP
.B Ctrl+e
Jump to end of line (instead of clicking line end)  
.TP
.B Ctrl+b
Move back one character (instead of left arrow)
.TP
.B Ctrl+f
Move forward one character (instead of right arrow)
.TP
.B Ctrl+w
Delete word before cursor (instead of backspace on word)
.TP
.B Ctrl+u
Clear line before cursor (instead of selecting and delete)
.SS Vim-Style (Recommended)
.TP
.B Esc
Enter normal mode - disable arrow keys temporarily
.TP
.B h
Move left
.TP
.B j  
Move down
.TP
.B k
Move up  
.TP
.B l
Move right
.TP
.B w
Word forward
.TP
.B b
Word back
.TP
.B 0
Beginning of line
.TP
.B $
End of line
.TP
.B dd
Delete entire line
.TP
.B yy
Yank (copy) line
.TP
.B p
Paste
.TP
.B u
Undo
.TP
.B Ctrl+r
Redo
.SH BASIC COMMANDS
.SS File Operations
.TP
.B ls
List files in current directory
.TP
.B ls -la
List all files with details
.TP
.B cd [dir]
Change directory
.TP
.B pwd
Print working directory
.TP
.B cat [file]
Display file contents
.TP
.B mkdir [name]
Create directory
.TP
.B rm [file]
Remove file
.TP
.B cp [src] [dst]
Copy file
.TP
.B mv [src] [dst]
Move/rename file
.SS Process Management
.TP
.B ps
List processes
.TP
.B top
System monitor
.TP
.B kill [pid]
Terminate process
.SS Text Editing
.TP
.B vim [file]
Open vim editor
.TP
.B nano [file]
Simple editor
.TP
.B echo [text]
Print text
.SH KEYBINDING CHEATSHEET
.PP
.nf
Movement:
  h j k l     - left down up right
  w b         - word forward back
  0 $         - line start end
  gg G        - file start end

Editing:
  i a        - insert before after cursor
  o A        - new line below above
  dd yy      - delete copy line
  p P        - paste below above
  u Ctrl+r   - undo redo

Search:
  / ?        - search forward back
  n N        - next previous match
  * #        - search word under cursor

Terminal:
  Ctrl+z     - background
  Ctrl+c     - interrupt
  Ctrl+d     - exit
  Ctrl+l     - clear screen
.fi
.SH OPTIONAL PRACTICE
.PP
To practice mouse-free navigation:
.PP
1. Disable mouse in terminal: Right-click > Disable Mouse
.PP  
2. Use only keyboard for navigation
.PP
3. Start with vimtutor: Run \fBvimtutor\fR
.PP
Remember: This is an OPTION. Use the mouse anytime you prefer.
.SH FILES
.TP
~/.c-school/profile    - User settings
~/.c-school/progress   - Learning progress
.SH SEE ALSO
cschool(1), linux(1), vim(1), man(7)
.SH VERSION  
C-SCHOOL 1.0 - Section 420 (Education)